The paper deals with compressive sensing and image reconstruction, which are core topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of a liquid-crystal-on-silicon modulator suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and optics (cs.OH). Finally, the incorporation of side information in the form of RGB images indicates a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SI).
